\begin_layout Subsection*
c) Derive and discuss the News Impact Curve (NIC) for the NAGARCH model.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The News Impact Curve (NIC) for the NAGARCH model is given by the conditional
 variance 
\begin_inset Formula $\sigma_{t}^{2}$
\end_inset

 as a function of the past squared shocks 
\begin_inset Formula $\varepsilon_{t-1}^{2}$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Therefore, the NIC for the NAGARCH model is given by the following expression:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align*}
\sigma_{t}^{2}\left(\varepsilon_{t-1}^{2}\right) & =\omega+\alpha\left(\varepsilon_{t-1}+\gamma\right)^{2}+\beta\sigma_{t-1}^{2}\\
 & =\omega+\alpha\left(\varepsilon_{t-1}^{2}+\gamma^{2}+2\varepsilon_{t-1}\gamma\right)+\beta\sigma_{t-1}^{2}\\
 & =\omega+\alpha\gamma^{2}+\beta\sigma_{t-1}^{2}+\alpha\left(\varepsilon_{t-1}^{2}+2\varepsilon_{t-1}\gamma\right)\\
 & =A+\alpha\left(\varepsilon_{t-1}^{2}+2\varepsilon_{t-1}\gamma\right)
\end{align*}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
where 
\begin_inset Formula $A\equiv\omega+\alpha\gamma^{2}+\beta\sigma^{2}$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The NAGARCH model extends the standard GARCH model by allowing for asymmetry
 in the response of the conditional variance to positive and negative shocks.
 This is achieved through the parameter 
\begin_inset Formula $\gamma$
\end_inset

, which allows the model to capture the asymmetry in the relationship between
 the past squared shocks and the current conditional variance.
 
\begin_inset Formula $\gamma$
\end_inset

 allows us the model differences between positive and negative news.
 
\end_layout

